<Author>1SusiQ
<Content>Awesome Location-Great Staff-Good Value First of all, when it comes to Hollywood Orchid Suites, location is the name of the game! Just go out the front door, up a little walkway to your right, and you're in the Hollywood-Highland shopping complex, which houses three stories of retail stores. It's Babylon Courtyard looks like a Hollywood set, complete with giant elephant sculptures. Viewing bridges at the back of the courtyard offer a great photo-op of the Hollywood Sign. There is a wide variety of places to eat. Our favorite was the California Pizza Kitchen. (The lettuce wraps and the Waldorf Salad were awesome!) One of the stores that we frequented was a Kodak camera shop. Everytime we filled up a memory card, we would have them transfer the photos onto a CD (for $9.95). Take the escalator down to the street level and you're right next to Grauman's Chinese Theatre, the main entrance to the Kodak Theatre (Emmy's, American Idol), a movie theater, the El Capitan Theater (Jimmy Kimmel), the Walk of Fame, the wax museum, Mel's Drive-In, some of the best souvenir shops in town, and so much more!We spent one full day at Universal Studios. It took us about 8 minutes to drive there and park. (By the way, we recommend splurging on a Front of the Line Pass! No waiting in lines and you get to go behind the scenes on various attractions). Allow some time for Universal's City Walk also. There are LOTS of neat shops and restaurants. If you like Italian food, Buca di Beppo is fantastic for both food and atmosphere! If you like seafood, one just can't beat Bubba Gump Shrimp Co. We recommend their Bucket O' Boat Trash!On a separate day, we made the short drive over to Beverly Hills.Be sure to take the trolley tour around town. It only costs $5.00 and is full of photo-ops!!!All of the staff at the Hollywood Orchid Suites were personable and accommodating! Our favorite was Adam at the front desk! He really made our day with his wonderful attitude and smile!The hotel itself, as noted in many reviews, is rather tired and worn, but it was clean and entirely adequate for our needs. (Just keep in mind that it is a 40-year-old converted apartment building.) We paid $119/night for a nice-sized room with two very comfortable queen-sized beds, a couch and coffee table, and a full kitchen with dining table. There are, of course, fancier accommodations in the area, but one would have to pay another $100-$200/night. It just isn't worth it, unless you will be spending more time in your room than seeing the sights.One of the main reasons we picked this hotel is because of the security features. Although we were two women, staying alone, we felt very safe here. One must have a keycard to use the elevators, the underground parking garage (parking is free), and the front door after hours.The pool was very clean and warm!The laundry room was a plus.The vending machines had a nice assortment of snacks/drinks.Don't forget to visit the rooftop garden. It's a nice place to relax.We hope you enjoy your stay at the Hollywood Orchid Suites as much as we did!We can't wait to return next year! 
