<Content>An island of calm in a sea of madness Imagine the madness of Hollywood  Highland, the mall, the Kodak Theatre, the Chinese Theatre, the throngs of tourists and crazy characters...then imagine walking through the mall, out the back exit and into a quiet leafy street, where your hotel is 20 yards away. That hotel is the Hollywood Orchid Suites - an island of calm in a sea of madness. You don't just get a room, you get a complete kitchen, and I mean complete...fridge, cooker, microwave, toaster oven, sink, all the cutlery, crockery and pots and pans you will need. Thus you can make your own meals if you don't like the stodgy fare of Mel's, Denny's etc. You get a pool that seems barely used, so you can probably have it to yourself if you want it. All this for only $99 + tax per night. Of course there are catches - the peaceful calm of Orchid Avenue is broken in the early hours by the delivery trucks to the mall, if you're on that side of the hotel. The rooms are clean and fully functional, but not modern. There aren't many channels on the TV. Between the tall buildings, the pool gets about 2 hours of sunshine a day. But these are minor niggles. If you have a car, there is free secure underground parking, if you don't, you have easy access to the Metro Red Line and a host of bus routes. Either way you have the world's greatest city on your doorstep. I recently spent 11 nights here and didn't want to go home. However, if sparkling luxury is what you're after, the Renaissance is across the road for three times the price. 
